CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1959, pg. 28, reads: "Classy - Above are players on the Paul Lumber and Supply Company Cardinals baseball team. The club is a member of the Uptown Hill City Little League.  Left to right, front row: Melvin Jackson, Delmar Morton, Kenneth King, Paul Wooden, Edward Maye, Dennis McFarland and Gary Griggs.  Back row: Harold Confer, Fred Green, Anthony Austin, Manager William Ralls, David Debasdelaben, Louis Davenport, Philmore Austin and Harvey Duncan. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Cardinals "Cards" Terrace Village Little League baseball team, front row from left: Melvin Jackson, Delmar Morton, Kenneth King, Paul Wooden, Edward Maye, Dennis McFarland, Gary Griggs; back row: Harold Confer, Fred Green, Anthony Austin, Manager William Ralls, David Debasdelaben, Louis Davenport, Philmore Austin, and Harvey Duncan, posed on field
